<li>HilD , HilC , and RtsA are homologous AraC family transcription factors .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24375101" target="_blank">24375101</a>]<br></li>
<li>These proteins belong to families of well-characterized transcription factors such as the AraC / XylS-like Hil proteins encoded by SPI-1 ( Schechter and Lee , 2001 ) and the two-component regulator pair SsrA and SsrB , encoded by SPI-2 ( Cirillo et al. , 1998 ; Hensel et al. , 1998 ; Garmendia et al. , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16999831" target="_blank">16999831</a>]<br></li>
