				<div class="SIT"><br><ul><li>Dimerization occurs between adjacent DNA sites when AraC binds arabinose .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>Hence , AraC likely binds with similar DNA sequence speciﬁcity across all Enterobacteriaceae species .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>AraC recognizes 17-bp half-sites that are separated by 4 bp ( 5 ) , which is almost equivalent to our 19-bp half-sites separated by 1 or 2 bp .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7730263" target="_blank">7730263</a>]<br></li>
