<li>Our reporter fusions indicate that maximal repression by AraC requires sequence between 1 and 15 relative to the transcription start site ( Fig. 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>We propose that AraC bound at this site interacts with additional regulatory proteins , perhaps another monomer of AraC , bound closer to the transcription start site .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
