<li>The non-LysR-type transcription activator AraC is an interesting exception to this rule and has been shown to bind to half-sites arranged as either inverted or direct repeats , with a preference for the latter arrangement in the presence of an inducer ( 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7730263" target="_blank">7730263</a>]<br></li>
